data.title: Meet Karina with @nanapurasperu a featured shop in our New Americans International Market she will be here Friday 5/17 during our Night...
data.meta_description:
millcreekcommon on May 16, 2024: "Meet Karina with @nanapurasperu a featured shop in our New Americans International Market she will be here Friday 5/17 during our Night Market from 5:00pm - 9:00pm.
We invite you to pop inside the public market to meet her and experience the items in her shop! 

Nanapuras has been a family business for over 40 years originating in Peru. Karina was born in Lima, her mother is from Arequipa on the coast of Peru. When Karina was 7 she and her mother started the business selling from a small stand in Lima. 

Since then, they have worked hand to hand with relatives and Peruvian artisans making beautiful alpaca and sheep wool pieces. Today she is teaching her daughters to admire and love their origins so that in the future they can continue with the family business.".
